700089f-a.title: Bronx: 143rd Street - Brook Avenue
700089f-a.text:
Views 1, 2 and 3.
E. 143rd Street, west from Brook Svenue, showing, in a

March 9, 1937

700090f-a.title: Bronx: 143rd Street - Brook Avenue
700090f-a.text:
East 143rd Street, west from Brook Avenue. The sign,in the
foreground, indicates that the W.P.A. is going to start improvement
activities here.
March 9, 1937
W.P.A. Photo
Five Boroughs Project
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE

700088f-b.title: Bronx: 143rd Street - Brook Avenue
700088f-b.text:
East 143rd Street, east from No. 475 (west of Brook Avenue),
showing where the W.P.A. is going to conduct improvement activities.
In the right background is seen St. Francis Hospital, extending from
Brook to St. Anns Avenues, and directly opposite it is partially seen
St. Joseph's Hospital.
March 9, 1937
W.P.A. Photo
Five Boroughs Project
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE
(2)
Viewing in the same direction from No. 491 and across
Brook Avenue. St. Joseph's Hospital is seen more prominently on
the left.
March 9, 1937
